<text id="04-procedure" title="bun-runtime Procedure" version="1.1.0" est_tokens="700" depth="medium">
  <summary>Five-step migration to a Bun-based JS/TS service.</summary>
  <section title="Steps">
    <section title="Step 1 — Pin Bun">
      <list>
        <item>Add `"packageManager": "bun@X.Y.Z"` to package.json.</item>
        <item>Pin `bun-version` in CI workflow.</item>
        <item>Commit `bun.lockb`.</item>
      </list>
    </section>
    <section title="Step 2 — Wire tsconfig">
      <list>
        <item>Set `moduleResolution: "bundler"`, `verbatimModuleSyntax: true`.</item>
        <item>Drop ts-node from devDependencies.</item>
      </list>
    </section>
    <section title="Step 3 — bunfig">
      <list>
        <item>Create bunfig.toml with `[install] frozen-lockfile = true` and `[test] coverage = true`.</item>
      </list>
    </section>
    <section title="Step 4 — Server">
      <list>
        <item>Author `src/server.ts` using `Bun.serve` (or Hono on top).</item>
        <item>Drop any `node:http` imports.</item>
      </list>
    </section>
    <section title="Step 5 — CI">
      <list>
        <item>Workflow uses `oven-sh/setup-bun@v2` with pinned `bun-version`.</item>
        <item>Run `bun install --frozen-lockfile &amp;&amp; bun test &amp;&amp; bun run build`.</item>
      </list>
    </section>
  </section>
</text>
